The paper discusses the use of wireless communication networks for data processing, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a game theoretic approach to incentivize agents to perform tasks for controllers, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of controllers and agents in a hierarchical structure also suggests a possible connection to distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses future research directions in this emerging area, which could potentially fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
